## **Diagnosing empty CMS pages (checklist)**

When a Strapi-backed page shows no items but Strapi admin has content:

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Confirm `NEXT_PUBLIC_TENANT_ID` matches entries' `tenant.tenantId` in Strapi |
| 2 | Query API with **URL slug** — note if `data: []` with **200** |
| 3 | Query with **stored Strapi slug** (e.g. `kalpana-2025-mo2`) or **parent year** |
| 4 | Compare counts — if year/parent filter returns rows, implement slug → semantic fallback |
| 5 | Verify **Published** / `publishedAt` where applicable (Kalpana documents use `draftAndPublish: false`) |
| 6 | Verify PDF/media populate — use [`getMediaUrl`](mdc:src/app/mosc-redesign/(syro)/directory/lib/strapiMedia.ts) for Strapi 4/5 shapes |

**Re-upload is rarely needed** when media URLs resolve in Strapi (`/uploads/...pdf`) and relations point to the correct parent year.

